# AutoSEO Engine - MVP Walkthrough

## Status
- **Core Engine**: Running (NestJS + SQLite)
- **Database**: SQLite (`autoseo.sqlite`) working efficiently.
- **Queue**: In-Memory (No Redis required).
- **Crawler**: Playwright integrated and active.

## How to Run
1.  **Frontend**: None yet (API Only).
2.  **Backend**:
    ```powershell
    cd autoseo-engine/core
    npm run start:dev
    ```

## How to Test
### 1. Register a Site & Start Crawl
Send a POST request to the API:
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/sites \
     -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
     -d '{"url": "https://example.com"}'
```

### 2. Check Results
Data is saved to `autoseo.sqlite`. You can view it using any SQLite viewer.
Or check logs to see "Processed https://example.com...".

## Project Structure
- `src/modules/crawler`: The scanning logic.
- `src/modules/queue`: The task manager.
- `src/modules/sites`: The entity manager.
